author: CNN
description: Hours after Ben & Jerry’s co-founder Jerry Greenfield resigned from the ice cream company he founded nearly five decades ago, his former business partner, Ben Cohen, revealed to CNN why Jerry felt he had to leave.
title: Ben Cohen explains why his co-founder quit Ben & Jerry's

author: CNN
description: The Federal Reserve cut its benchmark interest rate Wednesday for the first time since December and signaled more cuts are likely this year. #CNN #News
title: Fed announces interest rates cuts amid signs of labor market weakness

author: CNN
description: An Air Traffic Controller scolded a Spirit Airlines pilot after the plane came within eight miles of Air Force One. President Trump was on his way to the UK when the incident occurred. CNN’s Omar Jimenez reports.
title: Controller scolds Spirit Airlines pilot to ‘pay attention’

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump called his second state visit to the UK “one of the highest honors of my life” during a banquet toast Wednesday night that hailed the close historic relationship between the US and Britain.
title: Trump's toast at royal dinner calls to defend value of the 'english-speaking'

author: CNN
description:
At least two people are in serious condition in central Pennsylvania in a shooting that involved police.

“WellSpan York Hospital is currently treating two individuals related to the police incident in North Codorus Township,” a hospital spokesperson said in a statement. “Both are in serious condition. Enhanced security protocols are in place at the hospital.” #CNN #News
title: At least 2 in serious condition in central Pennsylvania shooting

author: CNN
description: More Americans think that having three or more kids is "ideal for a family." CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down the polling numbers. #CNN #News
title: What's the ideal American family size? Harry Enten looks at public opinion

author: CNN
description: Dr. Debra Houry, who recently resigned as the CDC’s chief medical officer, tells a Senate hearing that CDC leadership is now comprised of 80% officials serving in an acting capacity due to retirements, firings, or resignations. #cnn #news #health #cdc
title: Ex-official on CDC losing career leaders

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump have been spending the day at Windsor Castle on their historic second state visit to Britain. The pomp and splendor of a royal occasion was on full display as King Charles III and Queen Camilla welcomed the Trumps and joined them for a carriage ride before lunch. While Trump is at Windsor, protesters are being kept at a distance. However, thousands of people gathered in central London to protest the president’s state visit.

CNN White House reporter Alayna Treene and royal correspondent Max Foster report from Windsor, England. #CNN #News
title: Pomp and grandeur on full display as royal family hosts Trumps in Windsor

author: CNN
description: The Federal Reserve cut its benchmark interest rate Wednesday for the first time since December and signaled more cuts are likely this year.
title: The 'clear message' Fed is sending with interest rate cut

author: CNN
description: American tennis player Taylor Townsend is apologizing for making negative comments about food served in China. Townsend posted several videos to her Instagram Story from the Shenzhen city of China, drawing backlash across social media.
title: Tennis star faces backlash after comments on Chinese food

author: CNN
description:
The Federal Reserve cut its benchmark interest rate for the first time since December, lowering the rate by a quarter of a percentage point, matching Wall Street expectations. The Fed signaled more cuts are likely this year.

CNN senior reporter Matt Egan reports from Federal Reserve headquarters, and CNN's Boris Sanchez speaks with Aaron Klein, deputy Treasury secretary in the Obama administration. #CNN #News
title: Federal Reserve cuts rates for the first time this year

author: CNN
description:
Israel says it has launched a ground offensive into Gaza City. The incursion has been with backlash from international organizations and the families of hostages held by Hamas. The Israeli military expects the operation will take “several months” to complete. 

CNN's Becky Anderson speaks with Gaza aid worker Hanya Aljamal about the situation. #CNN #News
title: Gaza aid worker: 'We are seeing an unprecedented humanitarian disaster that could be easily avoided'

author: CNN
description: Democratic Rep. Pramila Jayapal accused FBI Director Kash Patel of creating a “giant cover-up” of the Epstein files after suddenly discovering “Donald Trump’s name was all over these files.” The congresswoman’s questioning led to a heated shouting match. #cnn #news #politics
title: See shouting match after lawmaker accuses Patel of Epstein cover-up

author: CNN
description:
A week after conservative activist Charlie Kirk was killed at Utah Valley University, students returned to campus. Tyler Robinson, the 22-year-old shooting suspect, confessed to his roommate that he had committed the murder, according to charging documents. 

Pamela Brown speaks with CNN legal analyst Carrie Cordero about the evidence in the case. #CNN #News
title: Officials: Kirk suspect's mom said he became more political & leaned left

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Kaitlan Collins talks to music legend Willie Nelson about a surprising memory from a 1979 White House visit with President Jimmy Carter’s son. Nelson is set to perform this weekend at the 40th annual Farm Aid festival, along with Neil Young, John Mellencamp, Dave Matthews and more. "Farm Aid 40" airs live on Saturday, September 20 at 7p ET on CNN.
title: How Willie Nelson smoked weed on the White House roof

author: CNN
description:
The widow of Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny says he was poisoned in a Siberian penal colony. Yulia Navalnaya says that tests of smuggled samples were carried out by two separate overseas laboratories, and that both reached the same conclusion. Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov said during a press conference Wednesday that he was "unaware" of the claim. 

CNN correspondent Clare Sebastian reports from London. #CNN #News
title: Widow of Russian opposition figure Alexey Navalny says he was poisoned in prison

author: CNN
description: Rep. Jamie Raskin asked FBI Director Kash Patel why more documents haven’t been released in the investigation into late convicted sex trafficker Jeffrey Epstein. #cnn #news #politics
title: Patel defends handling of Epstein files in fiery exchange

author: CNN
description: Sen. Rand Paul grilled former CDC director Dr. Susan Monarez about the agency's vaccine recommendations during a Senate committee hearing about her abrupt firing. #CNN #News
title: Sen. Paul, ex-CDC director spar during hearing

author: CNN
description: The widow of former Russian opposition figure Alexey Navalny, Yulia Navalnaya, has claimed in a video on social media that she has proof her husband was poisoned. Navalnaya claims to have smuggled biological material from where her husband had been held and that tests by two laboratories came to the same conclusion. The Kremlin says it is "unaware" of the accusations. CNN's Clare Sebastian reports.
title: Navalny’s widow says lab tests prove he was poisoned

author: CNN
description:
Israel said it launched an expanded ground assault on Gaza City on Tuesday in defiance of international condemnation, as Palestinians fled the enclave’s largest urban area in waves amid escalating bombardment. The moves come as an independent UN inquiry concluded that Israel is committing genocide in Gaza, finding, in part, that civilians in the battered enclave “were targeted collectively due to their identity as Palestinians.”
CNN's Jeremy Diamond reports. #CNN #News
title: Israel says its invasion of Gaza City has begun

author: CNN
description: In an interview with CNN’s Chief White House Correspondent Kaitlan Collins, Deputy Attorney General Todd Blanche defended President Trump’s suggestion that protesters who confronted him at a DC restaurant could face criminal charges. #CNN #News
title: Deputy AG defends Trump’s idea of prosecuting DC protesters

author: CNN
description:
Dance breaks, comedy sketches, a two-hour time limit. No bunts, walks or mound visits. Banana Ball is selling out stadiums around the country.

CNN's John Berman and Kate Bolduan speak with Savannah Bananas left fielder RobertAnthony "Coach RAC" Cruz about the appeal of Banana Ball. #CNN #News
title: Inside Banana Ball: The Savannah Bananas barnstorming team selling out stadiums

author: CNN
description: An independent United Nations inquiry has concluded for the first time that Israel has committed genocide against Palestinians in Gaza, and that the country’s top leaders have incited genocide. The accusation has previously been made by other organizations, including the International Association of Genocide Scholars and two leading Israeli human rights groups. Israel has strongly denied the claims. CNN’s Jomana Karadsheh reports. #C  NN #news
title: UN commission says Israel is committing genocide in Gaza

author: CNN
description: Former President Barack Obama spoke about the assassination of conservative activist Charlie Kirk at an event in Erie, Pennsylvania.
title: Obama responds to the assassination of Charlie Kirk

author: CNN
description: Dr. Susan Monarez, former director of the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, tells a Senate committee that US Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. required that all CDC policy and personnel decisions be cleared by political staff. #CNN #News
title: Ex-CDC director: RFK Jr. put politics over science

author: CNN
description: Dr. Susan Monarez makes her opening statement before members of the Senate Health, Education, Labor and Pensions Committee on Capitol Hill.  Monarez said she was fired by Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr.  just 29 days into her tenure as CDC director for not agreeing to sign off on vaccine recommendations without first seeing evidence. #CNN #News
title: ‘I was fired for holding the line’: Ousted CDC director testifies about RFK Jr. dismissing her

author: CNN
description: During President Donald Trump's first state visit to the United Kingdom in 2019, protestors flew a large, bright orange balloon depicting the president as a baby. Co-creator of the so-called "Trump Baby", Leo Murray, says that the protest at the first visit was a moment of jubilation, but asks: "is it funny now?"
title: Trump Baby Blimp Creators Say the Joke Doesn’t Land Anymore

author: CNN
description:
Former President Barack Obama commented on the assassination of conservative activist Charlie Kirk, saying that “regardless of where you are on the political spectrum, what happened to Charlie Kirk was horrific and a tragedy.”

CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Gov. Andy Beshear (D-KY) about Obama's comments, public health and his own political future.  #CNN #News
title: Gov. Beshear: When we try to use violence for politics 'we lose the chance to declare our humanity'

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten takes a look at Attorney General Pam Bondi’s popularity after she said the Justice Department would “absolutely target you, go after you, if you are targeting anyone with hate speech, anything, and that’s across the aisle.”  #CNN #News
title: 'A disaster for Pam Bondi’: Enten on the AG’s ‘hate speech’ comments

author: CNN
description:
President Trump says he has reached a deal to save TikTok from being banned in the United States, which was part of a bipartisan law passed by Congress. Sources say a new company to operate the app in the US would be made up of an 80% consortium of American companies and 20% Chinese companies. The deal hasn't been finalized yet.

CNN media correspondent Hadas Gold reports. #CNN #News
title: Trump says he has reached a deal to save TikTok from US ban

author: CNN
description: The seasons are changing, but not as they normally do. Fall is getting warmer and that’s pushing back the date of the average first freeze and decreasing autumn snowfall for much of the United States. #cnn #news #weather
title: Fall's first freeze isn't arriving on schedule for most of the US. Here's why

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump arrived via Marine One at Windsor Castle and were greeted by the Prince and Princess of Wales before meeting King Charles III and Queen Camilla. #CNN #news
title: Trump meets King Charles at Windsor Castle

author: CNN
description: US President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump have arrived at Windsor Castle as they kick off their first full day of a historic second state visit to Britain.  #CNN #News
title: See Trump’s royal welcome at Windsor Castle

author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson argued that leaders shouldn't call political opponents "Nazis, Fascists, and enemies of the state." But President Trump has a history of using that same rhetoric when it comes to Democrats he doesn't like. #CNN #News
title: GOP criticizes the left for using same rhetoric as Donald Trump

author: CNN
description: From Nepal to Indonesia, protestors are waving the pirate flag from “One Piece”, the best-selling Japanese manga. CNN's Hanako Montgomery explains why it's become a global banner of anger and defiance. #cnn #news #onepiece #indonesia #nepal #france #philippines #protest
title: Why the ‘One Piece’ flag is flown at protests

author: CNN
description: In a video shared by the Hostages and Missing Families Forum, Einav Zangauker, the mother of Israeli hostage Matan Zangauker is seen outside Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's house, yelling in anguish, apparently addressing the PM's wife Sara. #CNN #news
title: Mother of Israeli hostage protests in front of PM Netanyahu's residence

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Kaitlan Collins interviews Deputy Attorney General Todd Blanche about President Trump and senior White House officials’ threats to investigate left-wing groups in the wake of Charlie Kirk’s assassination. #CNN #News
title: ‘Not going to name groups’: Deputy attorney general on left-wing groups being targeted by DOJ

author: CNN
description: Charging documents show the suspect confessed in a series of messages sent to his roommate after the attack. Robinson’s mother said he had become more political and leaned left, “becoming more pro-gay and trans-rights oriented.” Robinson “began to date his roommate, a biological male who was transitioning genders,” his mother said, according to court documents. #CNN #News
title: Court documents: Suspect confessed to killing Kirk in a series of messages

author: CNN
description: Utah County Attorney Jeff Grey read aloud text messages sent by Tyler Robinson, the suspect in the killing of Charlie Kirk, and his roommate.
title: Texts between Kirk shooting suspect and roommate revealed

author: CNN
description: Four people have been arrested after a group of political activists projected images meant to draw attention to President Donald Trump’s relationship with Jeffrey Epstein onto the walls of Windsor Castle, authorities said. The Thames Valley police said the four adults, who were not immediately identified, were arrested on “suspicion of malicious communications following a public stunt in Windsor.” They remained in custody late Tuesday evening in the United Kingdom. #CNN #News
title: Epstein scandal haunts Trump's UK visit as 4 arrested for projecting images onto Windsor castle
